# Rendered carousel slides accumulate on local disk during dev/testing and
# have no business in a deployment — production uses Vercel Blob storage
# (BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN) instead of the local public/carousels dir. Without
# this, hundreds of MB of locally-generated preview images get swept into
# every serverless function that touches the render pipeline, blowing past
# Vercel's 250MB uncompressed function size limit.
apps/control-plane/public/carousels/
output/
